data.enText: to enter a country, town, etc. using military force in order to take control of it

data.chText: 军队是在那年的8月9日入侵的。
data.enText: Troops invaded on August 9th that year.

data.chText: 古罗马人是何时侵略英国的？
data.enText: When did the Romans invade Britain?

data.chText: （尤指造成损害或混乱地）涌入；侵袭
data.enText: to enter a place in large numbers, especially in a way that causes damage or confusion

data.chText: 大批示威者闯进了政府办公大楼。
比赛结束的哨声一响，球迷便开始冲入球场。
data.enText: As the final whistle blew, fans began invading the field.

data.chText: 癌细胞可能扩散到身体的其他部位。
data.enText: The cancer cells may invade other parts of the body.
to affect sth in an unpleasant or annoying way

data.chText: 新闻界有权以这种方式干扰她的私生活吗？
data.enText: Do the press have the right to invade her privacy in this way?

simple_means.memory_skill: in 进入 + vad 走，行 + e → 走进去 → 侵略

means: (尤指造成损害或混乱地)涌入

tr: march aggressively into another's territory by military force for the purposes of conquest and occupation
penetrate or assault, in a harmful or injurious way
example: The cancer had invaded her lungs

tr: to intrude upon, infringe, encroach on, violate
example: This new colleague invades my territory
The neighbors intrude on your privacy

tr: occupy in large numbers or live on a host
example: the Kudzu plant infests much of the South and is spreading to the North

value.def: To invade a country means to enter it by force with an army.

example.ex: In autumn 1944 the allies invaded the Italian mainland at Anzio and Salerno...
example.tran: 1944 年秋，盟军从安齐奥与萨勒诺攻入意大利本土。

example.ex: The Romans and the Normans came to Britain as invading armies.
example.tran: 罗马人以及诺曼人通过军事入侵来到英国。

value.def: If you say that people or animals invade a place, you mean that they enter it in large numbers, often in a way that is unpleasant or difficult to deal with.

example.ex: People invaded the streets in victory processions almost throughout the day...
example.tran: 几乎一整天,大街上都挤满了欢庆胜利的游行队伍。

example.ex: Every so often the kitchen would be invaded by ants.
example.tran: 厨房常常会遭到大批蚂蚁的进犯。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to walk, to go 走, 行
rootsaffixes.title: vad, vas

per 贯穿 + vad 走，行 + e → 贯穿着走 → 遍及
